      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "In shady slopes at higher altitudes, weak layers consisting of faceted crystals can be found deep in the snowpack. These are usually covered by compact or crusted can form layers of snow. Early in the morning, the snowpack at medium altitudes is frozen hard and firns in the sun during the day. Towards the ground, the snowpack is partly wet and can glide snow. In the foothills, the ground is increasingly pitting on the south side."
      },
